  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You summon three Constrictor Snakes (D20 Modern, p257), which emerge from your arms. Instead of making a weapon attack, you can direct a snake to strike a target within 15 feet. As a full-round action, you can direct all snakes to strike. The snakes attack with their natural weapon, using your attack bonuses (they count as melee weapons).<br><br>The snakes will retract back into your arm at the end of your next turn, at which point you suffer 1 point of temporary Strength damage (Fortitude DC 15 negates).</p>\n\n\n<p><b>Mastery:</b> The first through fourth steps decrease the Fortitude save DC to avoid Strength damage by 1.<br><br>The third step allows you to pay 4 additional Chakra and instead summon two snakes, each which 30 ft range and dealing 1d8+10 damage with their attacks.<br><br>The fifth step removes the Strength damage entirely.</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
